commit.message: Release v4.5

pyproject.toml support without setup.py

Fixes: #85

Support colons in the parser's format_usage() output.

The split around ":" only needs to separate the automatic "usage:" prefix, not
any colons (for example in "HOST:PORT" strings) that happen to be in the
output. Split just once to ensure this.
Release v4.4

Prefer 'prog=' in configuration over basename(pyfile)

Fixes: #79

Use the SPDX License format

https://spdx.org/licenses/Apache-2.0.html
spec: require python2-toml on Enterprise Linux 7

Fix the pyproject.toml manpages example

This fixes this error:
      running build_manpages
      error: 'manpages' option is required

Update repology badge

`argparse-manpage` entry in Repology will be merged into `python:argparse-manpage`

README.md: note that pre-written manpages must be in manifest

That is, man pages installed with ‘manfile’ must be listed in ‘MANIFEST.in’.
Release v4.3

prefer tomli over toml

Per discussion in:
https://github.com/praiskup/argparse-manpage/commit/c9f0ff6912bb7af888a057f3b61dc3145fffd19f

Closes: #92
Release v4.2
Add support for pre-written man pages (manfile option)

pylint: use packaging.version

Per warning:
Deprecated module 'distutils.version'
tests/test_examples.py: remove unused helper function
Tests: move pushd contextmanager to argparse_testlib and reuse it
Add support for pyproject.toml specification of manpages

Allow author details to come from just get_author_email()

When pyproject.toml is used, the author details seem to be set in just the
Distribution.get_author_email() method, while get_author() returns None.
Fix incorrect dict access for --include support
Relase v4.1
Switch tox-github-action from master to main branch
Add --include command-line flag
ci: fix Python diff linter

Allow to override build date with SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH

in order to make builds reproducible.
See https://reproducible-builds.org/ for why this is good
and https://reproducible-builds.org/specs/source-date-epoch/
for the definition of this variable.

This patch was done while working on reproducible builds for openSUSE.

Release v4

Fixes: #72
Formally deprecate 'build_manpage' module

Add argparse-manpage[setuptools] extra

Relates: #63
Fixes: #71

Manpage: don't require the data= option

The definition of the data= is blurry, and it's better to not use it
from the outside, it could change.  Try to hide it from users (make it
optional and private), and actually revert a change that the old
Manpage() API.

Relates: #7

setup: declare setuptools dependency

Fixes: #63
